{{Companies law}}

'''Enkeltpersonforetak''' (ENK) is a type of [[sole proprietorship]] in [[Norway]]. <ref>{{cite web
|url=https://www.altinn.no/no/Starte-og-drive-bedrift/Forberede/Velge-organisasjonsform/Enkeltpersonforetak/
|title=Enkeltpersonforetak
|publisher= Altinn
|date= November 25, 2014
|accessdate=October 8, 2015}}</ref>

The company is considered part of the personal assets of the owner, who holds the full juridical and economic [[Legal liability|liability]] of the company. The sole proprietorship entity holds a number of advantages, such as that there is no minimum [[Shareholders' equity|equity]], requirements for [[auditing]] or registration fee at the [[Brønnøysund Register Centre]]. Sole proprietorships do not have to have the two or three letter corresponding company type in the official company name. Instead they are required to have the [[surname]] of the proprietor somewhere in the company name.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.bedin.no/php/d_emneside_eng/cf/hApp_102/hPKey_1613/hParent_17/hDKey_2 | title=Self-employed Business | publisher=Ministry of Trade and Industry | date=3 March 2008 | accessdate=30 November 2011}}</ref>

